{"TENSE":[{"def":"One of the forms which a verb takes by inflection or by adding auxiliary words, so as to indicate the time of the action or event signified; the modification which verbs undergo for the indication of time.","pos":""}],"TENSIBILITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being tensible; tensility.","pos":""}],"TENSIBLE":[{"def":"Capable of being extended or drawn out; ductile; tensible.","pos":""}],"TENSILE":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to extension; as, tensile strength.","pos":""},{"def":"Capable of extension; ductile; tensible.","pos":""}],"TENSILITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being tensile, or capable of extension; tensibility; as, the tensility of the muscles.","pos":""}],"TENSION":[{"def":"The force by which a part is pulled when forming part of any system in equilibrium or in motion; as, the tension of a srting supporting a weight equals that weight.","pos":""},{"def":"Expansive force; the force with which the particles of a body, as a gas, tend to recede from each other and occupy a larger space; elastic force; elasticity; as, the tension of vapor; the tension of air.","pos":""}],"TENSIONED":[{"def":"Extended or drawn out; subjected to tension.","pos":""}],"TENSITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being tense, or strained to stiffness; tension; tenseness.","pos":""}],"TENSIVE":[{"def":"Giving the sensation of tension, stiffness, or contraction.","pos":""}],"TENSOR":[{"def":"A muscle that stretches a part, or renders it tense.","pos":""},{"def":"The ratio of one vector to another in length, no regard being had to the direction of the two vectors; -- so called because considered as a stretching factor in changing one vector into another.","pos":""}]}